# Testing And CI

- Use Node.js 24 or newer.
- Keep TypeScript strictness intact. Narrow indexed values, omit absent optional properties, use type-only imports, and include `.js` extensions for local ESM imports that run after compilation.
- Keep tests colocated as `*.test.ts` next to source files. Prefer dependency injection over module mocking.
- Run the smallest useful validation while iterating, then run the relevant full checks before finishing substantive code changes.
- Standard validation commands are `npm run format:check`, `npm run lint`, `npm run typecheck`, `npm run test`, and `npm run build`.
- Build before smoke-testing the CLI or changing PR-review workflows, because they import from `dist/`.
- CI runs format, lint, typecheck, build, and unit tests. There is no deploy, release, npm publish, or artifact pipeline yet.
